column5: Enjoying the nice temps and sunsnhine.Got all the windows open, and Im in the mood to hit the river.No not that river Terry,the Notty   . What a beauty of a day EH.
So then.......what are ya doin at home with the windows open then???  GO FISH!!!!

Ain' it a beauty. Finally over the worst of the flu and the sun comes out.  Got 1/2 a cord cut, split and stacked ( I was down to my last few sticks)  All dry even. Almost lopped off my toe but    I still gotta heat the house
last weekend in June maybe..LOL  got you hooked on flipping, EH
Aint no better rush then that.
Yup it's been a great day here in Oshawa also, nice to see the sides of the roads full of water and not snow!

Lovin It. Gonna have a nice steak on the BBQ this evening with a nice brown pop. All ready took out daughter for her first walk around the block. Taken the weekend offf to hit Bass Pro tomorrow. Life could not be better.
hold back the ice break-up 'til sunday ,,, just 'til sunday!!!  i'm not ready for ice-out yet!  damn sun-worshippers!
Bring on the tanning weather brother. Cant believe I just said that,but I cant wait to be slamming some fish,s in the warm sun.
Guess you're gonna have a rude awakening when winter comes back next Thursday eh....
Had the windows open too!  Now there's dust all over everything

warm weather is fine but I still gots to ice me some more brookies, lakers, walters and a few dirty snakes! Seeing as we still have over 3 ft of ice on some lakes I think I will be doin some tanning on the ice a few times yet!!!!!!
